Package game.grounds

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Spawnable
    Spawnable is an interface that describes Ground objects that can spawn other objects.
    Teleport
    Teleport is an interface that helps manages Ground objects (namely WarpPipes) that allow player to teleport to a different map.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Dirt
    The Dirt class is a class that represents bare dirt The Dirt class is a subclass of the Ground class
    Floor
    The Floor class is a class that represents the floor inside a building.
    Fountain
    The Fountain class is an abstract class that represents Magical Fountains.
    HealthFountain
    The HealthFountain class is a class that represents the Magical Fountain of Health.
    HighGround
    The HighGround class is an abstract class that represents high grounds.
    Lava
    The Lava class is a class that represents a blazing fire ground.
    Mature
    The Mature class is a class that represents the final stage of a tree's life cycle.
    PowerFountain
    The PowerFountain class is a class that represents the Magical Fountain of Power.
    Sapling
    The Sapling class is a class that represents the second stage of a tree's life cycle.
    Sprout
    The Sprout class is a class that represents the first stage of a tree's life cycle.
    TeleportManager
    The TeleportManager class is a singleton class that manages objects that implement Teleport interface, namely WarpPipes.
    Tree
    The Tree class is an abstract class that represent Trees and all its stages in its life cycle.
    Wall
    The Wall class is a class that represents a generic brick wall.
    WarpPipe
    The WarpPipe class is an abstract class that represents warp pipes in Super Mario, the green tubes.
